From: Armbian <info@armbian.com>
Date: Sat, 18 Jul 2026 00:00:01 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] configs: espressobin: enable hardware RNG (Turris rWTM TRNG)

The Armada 3720 exposes a TRNG through the CZ.NIC secure firmware (rWTM), which
Armbian builds from mox-boot-builder. Enable the driver so u-boot seeds entropy
from hardware. The RNG_TURRIS_RWTM Kconfig explicitly supports EspressoBin when
that secure firmware is used, and its deps (DM_RNG && ARMADA_3700) are already
met by this defconfig. Matches the espressobin-bootloader / -ultra configs; the
hardware RNG is common to the standard EspressoBin and the Ultra.

Signed-off-by: Igor Pecovnik <igor@armbian.com>
---
 configs/mvebu_espressobin-88f3720_defconfig | 2 ++
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+)

diff --git a/configs/mvebu_espressobin-88f3720_defconfig b/configs/mvebu_espressobin-88f3720_defconfig
--- a/configs/mvebu_espressobin-88f3720_defconfig
+++ b/configs/mvebu_espressobin-88f3720_defconfig
@@ -99,3 +99,5 @@
 # CONFIG_WATCHDOG_AUTOSTART is not set
 CONFIG_WDT=y
 CONFIG_WDT_ARMADA_37XX=y
+CONFIG_DM_RNG=y
+CONFIG_RNG_TURRIS_RWTM=y
